Black Friday 2019 takes place on 29 November, and many South African companies are taking advantage of this shopping day to attract consumers with great discounts. Black Friday is an American tradition and is seen as the start of the Christmas shopping season. In recent years, South African retailers have adopted Black Friday and have helped it to grow into the biggest online shopping day in the country. While Black Friday used to be focussed on online shopping in South Africa, many brick-and-mortar shops have now also joined the tradition. It is, however, not only traditional retailers who are offering Black Friday deals. Many telecoms operators and entertainment platforms are also offering discounts on their products. Here are great Black Friday tech and telecoms deals which are already available or have been unveiled by companies. *Please note that some of these deals will only be available to purchase from 29 November. Please click on the “Deal” links to learn more. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-329569" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/digicape2.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/digicape2.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/digicape2-595x400.png 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/digicape2-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-329571" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/digicape3.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/digicape3.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/digicape3-595x400.png 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/digicape3-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (m